# OknaPro Landing — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- HTML5 + Tailwind CSS v3 CDN + Vanilla JS ES5
- No npm, bundlers, frameworks, libs except Tailwind CDN
- Single file: index.html (+ policy.html if needed)

## HTML
- Semantic tags: header/main/section/article/footer/nav
- aria-label on interactive elements without visible text
- loading="lazy" decoding="async" on all <img> except LCP hero image
- id attributes only on nav anchors and JS hooks

## CSS
- Tailwind utility classes only, no inline styles
- Breakpoints: sm: md: lg: (mobile-first)
- Palette: sky-600 (accent), slate-900/700/600/200/100/50, white

## JS
- IIFE wrapper (function(){...})() for isolation
- ES5 only: var, function declarations, no arrow functions, no let/const
- addEventListener only, no onclick attributes

## Composer output rules
- Show ONLY changed fragments, never the full file
- Wrap each section edit in <!-- SECTION: name --> comment
- Never rewrite sections not mentioned in the task
- Never add new dependencies without explicit request
- Never add explanatory comments to obvious code
